===Etymology 1===
From {{inh|en|enm|drogge|t=medicine}}, from {{der|en|frm|drogue|t=cure, pharmaceutical product}}, from {{der|en|fro|drogue}}, {{m|fro|drocque|t=tincture, pharmaceutical product}}, from {{etyl|dum|en}} or {{der|en|gml|droge}}, as in {{m|dum|droge}} {{m|dum|vate|t=dry vats, dry barrels}}, mistaking {{m|dum|droge}} for the contents, which were usually dried herbs, plants or wares. ''Droge'' comes from {{der|en|dum|droghe|drōghe|t=dry}}, from {{der|en|odt|drōgi|t=dry}}, from {{der|en|gem-pro|*draugiz|t=dry, hard}}. Cognate with {{cog|en|dry}}, {{cog|nl|droog|t=dry}}, {{cog|de|trocken|t=dry}}.

